INSERT INTO "public"."posts" VALUES ('1441096659297523_1483781851695670', 'Fauna in Focus', null, 'Ky Sona and Dang Dim shared Fauna in Focus''s video.', null, 'We are happy to release part 2/12 "Ibis". The first stop on our journey is the Northern Plains and Dry Dipterocarp forests of Cambodia. The unique ecosystems around Tmat Bouey are home to two species of critically endangered ibis, the white-shouldered ibis and Cambodia''s National bird, the giant ibis. Here we learn about ecotourism efforts from Sam Veasna Center for Wildlife Conservation (SVC) and talk to local wildlife researchers from WCS Cambodia about their efforts to protect these amazing birds.

Over the coming weeks we will be releasing all the scenes from our film on Facebook and our Vimeo page here: https://vimeo.com/faunainfocus. The full film will also be made available online in June2017. We encourage you to share these film scenes with your friends and family, and help us spread awareness of wildlife and conservation across Cambodia. You will also be able to find all these videos on our website: 

http://www.faunainfocus.org/.

We would like to thank our current partners and sponsors at USAID Cambodia and Winrock International for supporting this Film Distribution Campaign, as well as all of our original film sponsors including Shinta Mani Foundation, Galveston Chapter of AAZK (GCAAZK) and the Endangered Species Foundation of New Zealand.

USAGE RIGHTS: You are welcome to share and repost this film anywhere on Facebook. If you would like to embed this film you can find it on our Vimeo page here: https://vimeo.com/album/4522543. If you would like to screen this film publicly for non-commercial, educational purposes please contact Fauna in Focus to organize a screening event. If you would like to download this film or use it for your own screening events or educational programs please contact us for a USAGE LICENSE. This film is copyrighted ©2016 by Fauna in Focus and Daniel Roper-Jones.

We would like to thank all of our amazing partner projects, including Sam Veasna Center for Wildlife Conservation (SVC), WCS Cambodia, BirdLife International Cambodia Programme, Banteay Srey Butterfly Centre, Wildlife Alliance, Monk''s Community Forestry Network, Elephant Valley Project, Fauna & Flora International - Cambodia Programme, BeTreed Adventures and Cambodian Entomology Initiatives - CEI.
Another special thanks to our film contributors including the amazing Oyen Rodriguez, Allan Michaud, Eddie Smith, Gilles Sainsily, Stephane De Greef, Peteris Tennison, and Terrence Cigler.

Final a special shout out to everyone who supported us back in 2015 when we first started filming, or helped out since then including Shinta Mani, Rosy Guesthouse, HAVEN Cambodia, The Little Red Fox Espresso, Sister Srey Cafe, Celliers d''Asie, Heritage Suites Hotel, Rambutan Hotel & Resort in Siem Reap - Cambodia, Navutu Dreams Resort & Wellness Retreat, Khmer Ways, Cambodia Vespa Adventures, Microlight Cambodia, Silk Screen Printing Lab, John McDermott, Big Wide World Photography, Grasshopper Adventures - Asia''s Best Bike Tours, The Hive Siem Reap, Belmiro''s Pizza & Subs, The Crocodile River Bistro, Johnny Orn, Aebe Christian De Boer, Jyoti Degroote, Stefania Pirani, Dyna Sovan Rattanak, Vichet Samrith Dickinson, Victoria Jones, and so many more we cannot possibly list them all here!', '2017-04-22T12:34:09+0000', 'Ky Sona', '1441096659297523', null, 'https://scontent.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t15.0-10/s130x130/17989200_1511242432250558_6722034687696437248_n.jpg?oh=8c0547259a77b85921f8d1e2c581bf30&oe=599A0248', '0', '3', '0', null, 'mobile_status_update', null, '', 'https://www.facebook.com/FaunainFocus/videos/1511096355598499/', null, null, '151770564864425_1511096355598499', '2');
